  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resources Admin Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Manage full spectrum of HR function in areas of recruitment, employee relations, payroll, report preparation & submission, etc</li><li>Manage end to end recruitment cycle including sourcing, arranging interview, salary proposal, on boarding process/orientation and exit interview.</li><li>Assist to manage employees’ matters in areas of compensation matters, appraisal for annual increment and performance bonus.</li><li>Manage HR Administrative duties in areas of preparation of all HR related letters, insurance, maintaining HR Documentation, etc</li><li>Processing and timely submission of Form IR21, NS claims, maternity claims, childcare claims, IR21, IR8A etc</li><li>Support employees in consultative guidance/mediation on HR policies, practices, and employee relations matters</li><li>Manage end-to-end onboarding & offboarding matters including but not limited to email, door access, documents and uniform</li><li>Process work pass applications, renewal & cancellations and liaise with Ministry of Manpower for work pass related issues.</li><li>Provide prompt update and accurate maintenance of employee database, organization charts, personal files as well as medical check-up and work pass renewals.</li><li>Assist in coordinating in training programme and liaise with nominated trainees on training requirements.</li><li>Preparation and submission of statutory, WICA and other relevant HR reports</li><li>Fulfil any government reporting requirements.</li><li>MOM Quarterly Survey</li><li>Government ad hoc survey on wages or retrenchment</li><li>General office administration and management</li><li>Manage and supervise the work of HR admin assistants</li><li>To undertake other HR function and ad-hoc assignments or duties as and when assigned from time to time.</li></ul><p><strong></strong><br /><strong>Job Requirement & Professional Qualifications</strong></p><p><ul><li><p>Diploma / Degree in Human Resource with at least 2 years of relevant HR experience</p></li><li><p>Good written and communication skills</p></li><li><p>Organized and Meticulous</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently.</p></li><li><p>Excellent Skill in Microsoft Office (Word/Excel)</p></li><li><p>Good knowledge of Employment Act</p></li><li><p>Experience with Work Passes application.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with MOM employment rules & regulation</p></li></ul></p>",
